
i) IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)
1. Meaning =           Cloud provider sirf infrastructure deta hai — jaise virtual machines, storage, networking.

2. Features =          Gives full control over infra resources such as virtual machine/storage etc., User ko servers aur infrastructure manage karna padta hai.

3. Admin Responsibility = You must take care of all the admin tasks such as: Patching, Upgrades, Backups

4. Pricing Model       = Pay-per-use

5. Examples            = EC2, VM, GCE 

6. Best Use Case       = Ideal choice for lift and shift migration and legacy application.



ii) PaaS (Platform as a Service)
1. Meaning  =    Cloud provider ek ready platform deta hai jahan application deploy aur develop kar sakte ho.

2. Features =    Give runtime environment/platform , To deploy application and development tools

3. Admin Responsibility  = Azure takes care of all the admin tasks including automated backups.

4. Pricing Model         = Pay-per-service model

5. Examples              = Azure Web App

6. Best Use Case         = Ideal choice where customer doesn’t want to take care of admin tasks.



iii) SaaS (Software as a Service)
1. Meaning              = Ready-made software directly users ko diya jata hai internet ke through.

2. Features             = Gives application access to the end users

3. Admin Responsibility = Azure takes care of all the admin tasks.

4. Pricing Model        = Pay-per-subscription model

5. Examples             = O365, Gmail, Dropbox etc.

6. Best Use Case        = Ideal choice where customer can use the standard version of a cloud application.